The paper deals with control and synchronization of multiagent systems, which are typically studied in the subfield of control systems (cs.SY) and multiagent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses distributed network controllers, which falls under the subfield of distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of symmetries in the nodes' vector fields is a common technique in the study of neural networks (cs.NE) and the paper also discusses consensus patterns, which is a topic in social networks (cs.SI).
